<P>
JOYCE CHEN; MANDARIN RESTAURATEUR, AUTHOR, TV HOST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joyce Chen, 76, who popularized Mandarin Chinese food in the United States 
through her restaurants, cookbook and TV shows.Born in Beijing, Chen fled the 
Communist regime with her husband and children in 1949 and settled in 
Cambridge, Mass. She opened the Joyce Chen Restaurant there in 1958. It not 
only was the first Mandarin Chinese restaurant in New England but became one of 
the best known Chinese restaurants in the country. Later, she wrote "The Joyce 
Chen Cook Book," and in the 1970s was host of "Joyce Chen Cooks," broadcast 
weekly on PBS. In Lexington, Mass., on Tuesday of the complications of 
Alzheimer's disease. 
</P>
