<P>
PAKISTANI BEHEADED FOR RAPING YOUNG BOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Pakistani was beheaded Friday in Mecca for kidnaping and raping a young boy, 
the Interior Ministry announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The announcement said the Pakistani seized the boy from a public street and 
took him to an isolated area. 
</P>
<P>
 The man was tried and convicted by a Sharia, or Islamic law, court. 
</P>
<P>
 Beheadings are carried out in public squares opposite mosques, usually Friday 
prayers. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 20 people have been beheaded this year, including Asians, Africans 
and Saudi nationals, mostly for smuggling and peddling drugs. 
</P>
