<TEXT>
<P>
 Euro Disney Stock Plunges: Trading of shares in the troubled leisure park were 
suspended for a quarter of an hour on the Paris bourse after they fell more 
than 10% on new doubts about the viability of the park outside Paris. The stock 
exchange halted trading in the early afternoon after the share hit $1.75, down 
from a closing price of $1.95 on Thursday.The Paris stock market stops trading 
in a share for 15 minutes if a price fluctuates 10%. A further suspension is 
carried out if the price moves another 5%. Euro Disney shares closed down 7.77% 
at $1.79 on heavy volume of 6.8 million shares. Brokers said the plunge was due 
to a report that Paribas Capital Markets leisure analyst Nigel Reed had valued 
the share at just 30 cents after a visit to the company. 
