<P>
 Natural Gas Prices Likely to Stay Soft: Spot natural gas prices reached their 
lowest levels in more than two years this week and are likely to stay low until 
winter because of growing supplies, analysts say. "I don't even think weather 
would help at this point unless a big hurricane hit," said Michael Barbis, an 
analyst at NatWest Securities in New York.Drilling rigs and pipelines in the 
Gulf of Mexico, a major gas-producing area, can be shut down or suffer damage 
from storms in the fall hurricane season. Spot market prices for natural gas 
along the Gulf Coast slumped this week to less than $1.50 per million British 
thermal units, the lowest level since April, 1992, and down 25 cents from 
earlier this month. A year ago, natural gas prices were at $2.25 per BTU. 
</P>
