<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; DEPUTY 
FATALLY WOUNDS MAN DURING STRUGGLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man shot by a sheriff's deputy near a park in Boyle Heights on Friday 
afternoon died later at Los Angeles County-USC Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The deputy was unhurt in the confrontation about 3:25 p.m. in the 600 block of 
Echandia Street, said sheriff's spokesman Ron Spear.  
</P>
<P>
 Spear said the deputy had been flagged down by people who told him of a 
beating in nearby Prospect Park. Before the deputy could get out of his patrol 
car "the suspect began attacking the deputy. During the struggle, one round 
discharged from the deputy's weapon," hitting the man, Spear said. 
</P>
<P>
 The dead man's name was withheld. 
</P>
</TEXT>
