<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS : OAK VIEW; UZI-ARMED GUNMAN SOUGHT IN ROBBERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lawmen were searching Friday for an Uzi-armed gunman who robbed two Oak View 
businesses, locking some of his victims in walk-in refrigerators.  
</P>
<P>
 In the latest robbery, about 4:45 p.m. Thursday, the man entered Scotty's 
Liquor at 910 N. Ventura Ave. and showed an Uzi automatic weapon to two clerks 
while demanding money, said Detective Susan Creede of the Ventura County 
Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The gunman locked the two in the store's walk-in refrigerator before fleeing, 
but they soon were able to get out, Creede said. The loss was estimated at 
about $400. 
</P>
<P>
 In a robbery thought to involve the same man, a gunman took $256 from Little 
Caesar's Pizza, 11420 N. Ventura Ave., on Monday. In that incident, the gunman 
handcuffed one teen-age cook to a pipe and locked a second in the freezer, 
Creede said. 
</P>
<P>
 The handcuffs were "like a toy," however, and the cook soon broke away and 
freed his colleague, the detective said. Both are 17-year-old Ojai boys. GREG 
RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
