<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS : OXNARD; BOY WHO FELL INTO POOL DIES AT HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 13-month-old boy who fell into a swimming pool at his Oxnard apartment 
complex has died, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Connor Bazillion, who fell into the pool Wednesday afternoon at Oxnard Shores 
at 5090 Nautilus St., was pronounced dead at 9:44 p.m. Thursday in the 
pediatric intensive care unit at Santa Barbara Cottage Hospital, representative 
Carla Brunstead said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire Capt. Curt Bensen, whose unit responded to the 911 call, said a man at 
the unit had dived into the pool after seeing the baby in the water. 
Dispatchers helped people at the scene in attempts to revive the child with 
CPR, Bensen said. 
</P>
<P>
 According to witness accounts, the child had wandered out of his apartment 
while his mother had slept. His father was identified as Paul Bazillion. GREG 
RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
