<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; EX-STUDENT'S INJURY CLAIM REJECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Conejo Valley Unified School District board has rejected a claim by a 
former Westlake High School student who was injured during an off-campus brawl 
in February. 
</P>
<P>
 The administrative claim filed by Curtis Simmons, 17, sought compensation for 
medical and general expenses resulting from the incident. 
</P>
<P>
 School board members rejected the claim at their meeting Thursday. President 
Dolores Didio said it is standard procedure for the board to reject all 
administrative claims. 
</P>
<P>
 The law requires plaintiffs to file claims before a lawsuit can be filed in 
Ventura County Superior Court. 
</P>
<P>
 Simmons' attorney, Judith Fogel, said she expected the board to reject the 
claim and added that her client will pursue a lawsuit. 
</P>
<P>
 Simmons, who school officials said will not return to Westlake High this year, 
was beaten with a wooden board Feb. 3 during a fight at North Ranch Park that 
left two other students hospitalized. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
