ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; GOLF TOURNAMENT TEE TIMES AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tee times are still available for a golf tournament that will benefit South 
County's only walk-in center for abused women. 
</P>
<P>
 The first annual Laura's House Golf Tournament will take place on Monday at 
the Pacific Golf Club, 200 Avenida la Pata, in San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 Money raised will go toward purchasing a shelter for women who are victims of 
domestic violence. The shelter will house abused women and offer educational 
programs on domestic violence. 
</P>
<P>
 Laura's House officials are asking for a donation of $150, which will cover 
entry fees for the tournament and an awards luau dinner afterward.  
</P>
<P>
 Organizers have collected more than $40,000 for the shelter fund. 
</P>
<P>
 In June, the doors opened for South County's first walk-in center for domestic 
violence victims at 97 Calle Industrias in the Ralph's shopping center off 
Avenida Pico . 
</P>
<P>
 Over the past three months, the center has helped several women. Volunteers 
drove one mother with children to court to obtain a restraining order while 
room in a temporary shelter was found for another woman. 
</P>
<P>
 Several support groups operate out of the center. Included are support groups 
for teens, women and the mothers of abused women. 
</P>
<P>
 For information about the tournament or any of the center's programs, call 
(714) 361-3775.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
