<P>
 The City Council has approved arts and culture grants for six regional groups 
for the 1994-1995 fiscal year. 
</P>
<P>
 The city's Arts Commission reviewed presentations by a variety of arts groups 
and chose the recipients based on who could offer the greatest benefit to 
residents, particularly children and senior citizens. 
</P>
<P>
 The grants, approved Monday, are: 
</P>
<P>
 * $4,000 to Opera Pacific to provide a series of educational programs for 
students, including a performance of "A Midsummer Night's Dream." 
</P>
<P>
 * $4,000 to the South Coast Repertory company for programs for elementary 
pupils. 
</P>
<P>
 * $3,500 to Ballet Pacifica for a high school-level program. 
</P>
<P>
 * $3,000 to the Pacific Symphony, for a 40 training clinics for Corona del Mar 
High School students and three ensemble performances at the Oasis Senior 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 * $2,000 to the Master Chorale for four quartet performances at schools. 
</P>
<P>
 * $2,000 to the Pacific Chorale for seven outreach programs for children's 
choruses directed at students in second through 12th grades. RUSS LOAR 
