<HEADLINE>
<P>
4 TEENS HURT IN CRASH NEAR HIGH SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four El Toro High School students were injured, one critically, when their 
Honda sedan collided with another car just after they pulled out of the 
school's parking lot, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The four boys were not identified because they are juveniles.The school was 
not in session, but the students had just left a cross-country training session 
as they pulled onto Ridge Route, according to Orange County Sheriff's Lt. Dan 
Martini.  
</P>
<P>
 The Honda and a Chevrolet collided on Toledo Lane. 
</P>
<P>
 Two of the most seriously injured teens were airlifted to Western Medical 
Center-Santa Ana, where one was reported in critical condition with head 
injuries and a second in guarded condition with broken bones. The other two 
teens were taken to Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center in Mission Viejo, 
where they were both reported in stable condition with broken bones, cuts and 
bruises.  
</P>
<P>
 The Chevrolet's driver was treated at Saddleback Memorial Medical Center in 
Laguna Hills and released. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no arrests or citations, Martini said, but the Sheriff's Department 
is investigating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
