<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONNORS RECEIVES 16-MONTH SENTENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ryan Connors, former star quarterback at Hart High, was sentenced Friday to 16 
months in prison following a drunk-driving crash that disfigured a 33-year-old 
music student and ruined his singing voice. 
</P>
<P>
 Connors, 20, had pleaded no contest to one count of causing great bodily 
injury while driving under the influence of alcohol and has been given until 
Sept. 6 to surrender. 
</P>
<P>
 Full story: Section B. 
</P>
