<HEADLINE>
<P>
FULLERTON'S LEE FINISHES SECOND IN PGA JUNIOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jenny Lee of Fullerton shot a four-under-par 68 Friday, the best final-round 
score in the girls' division of the PGA Junior Championship.But Beth Bauer of 
Brando, Fla., finished with a 70 to win by one shot. 
</P>
<P>
 Bauer didn't clinch the victory until the 18th hole, when she made par and Lee 
hit her second shot into the water. Bauer's 72-hole total was six-under 282. 
Grace Park of Phoenix was third at 287. 
</P>
</TEXT>
