<HEADLINE>
<P>
AFTERSHOCK WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TWO TEMBLORS: Two aftershocks of the Northridge earthquake shook the West 
Valley on Friday evening, seismologists said. The strongest temblor, of 3.3 
magnitude, hit at 9:12 p.m. and was centered two miles west-northwest of Canoga 
Park, according to Caltech seismologists. Previously, a 2.8 magnitude shock was 
registered at 5:28 p.m., also centered in Canoga Park. 
</P>
