<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: WOODLAND HILLS; TACO BELL DONATES $45,850 TO REPAIR POOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MANNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Taco Bell Foundation has donated $45,850 to the West Valley Family YMCA to 
help repair damage caused to its swimming pool by the Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The donation will be turned over at a special event Monday at 11 a.m. at the 
facility, 18810 Vanowen St., Reseda. 
</P>
<P>
 Julia Stewart, Taco Bell Corp.'s vice president for the MegaWest zone, will 
present a check to David Powell, West Valley Family YMCA executive director. 
</P>
<P>
 Rep. Anthony C. Beilenson (D-Woodland Hills), who helped arrange the donation, 
also will take part, as will City Councilwoman Laura Chick. 
</P>
<P>
 Taco Bell Corp. set up the foundation in 1992 to assist nonprofit 
organizations and often help with disaster relief, officials said. The 
foundation -- a separate entity from Taco Bell Corp. -- raised the money 
through employee contributions and donation canisters set up in stores 
throughout the nation. 
</P>
<P>
 Charities seeking aid from the foundation should write to Michele Myszka, 
executive director, Taco Bell Foundation, 17901 Von Karman Ave. Irvine, Calif., 
92714. FRANK MANNING 
</P>
</TEXT>
