<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; CABLE PROBLEM DISRUPTS POWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 About 1,500 Canyon Country residents were without power for a few hours early 
Friday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 An underground cable malfunctioned, disrupting power at 12:53 a.m. to 
residents in the North Oaks neighborhood, said Southern California Edison 
spokeswoman Christina Bradley. 
</P>
<P>
 Power was restored to 90% of the customers by 2:52 a.m., with the remainder by 
6:10 a.m., Bradley said. DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
