<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGION NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN DART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CENTER DEDICATION: Los Angeles Cardinal Roger M. Mahony will be the principal 
speaker Monday at 10 a.m. dedication ceremonies for the Catholic Charities 
Glendale Community Center, which will provide social services to youths, 
immigrants, troubled families and others in need. 
</P>
<P>
 The new building on San Fernando Road replaces an old Catholic Youth 
Organization (CYO) building that had become dilapidated and was torn down in 
1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Built with federal funds allocated by the city of Glendale, the center will be 
operated by the Catholic Charities department of the Los Angeles archdiocese. 
</P>
<P>
 LABOR DAY OBSERVANCE: Rep. Maxine Waters (D-Los Angeles) will talk about 
immigration issues and bills before Congress dealing with health care and jobs 
on Sept. 4 during the sixth annual San Fernando Valley Interfaith Council Labor 
Day Celebration in Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles City Councilman Richard Alarcon and John Perez, chair of the 
Valley Labor, Political and Education Council, will also speak. 
</P>
<P>
 Participating clergy include the Revs. Harry Adams, Chatsworth United 
Methodist Church; Charlotte Shivvers, Sepulveda Unitarian Universalist Society; 
Jeff Utter, Chatsworth Congregational Church, and Tiser Turner, Greater 
Community Baptist Church in Pacoima. 
</P>
<P>
 The observance at the Congregational Church of Northridge, 9659 Balboa Blvd., 
will begin at 7:30 p.m., preceded by a free barbecue at 6 p.m. For information, 
call (818) 718-6460. 
</P>
<P>
 HOLY DAYS MUSIC: Cantor Fran Lawson will perform at Temple Judea in Tarzana at 
9:30 p.m. today in a free concert introducing the music and themes of the 
approaching Jewish High Holy Days. 
</P>
<P>
 Lawson will be accompanied by a vocal quartet, piano, cello and flute in the 
program. The 10-day Jewish holiday begins on Labor Day with Rosh Hashana eve 
services. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the temple, 5429 Lindley Ave., at (818) 987-2616. 
</P>
<P>
 MIRTH & MUSIC: A musical service titled "Humor as a Spiritual Resource" will 
be presented at Emerson Unitarian Church on Sunday by guest vocalists Julie and 
Fred Land and Darcey Lober from the Conejo Valley Unitarian Universalist 
Fellowship. 
</P>
<P>
 The service, which begins at 10:30 a.m., is being held at the Canoga Park 
Senior Citizens Center, 7326 Jordan Ave. For information, call (818) 887-6101. 
</P>
<P>
 BAGEL BRUNCH: Volunteers are invited to enjoy free bagels Sunday while 
assembling packages of food for distribution to the needy at Sova, the kosher 
food pantry in a mini-mall at 6027 1/2 Reseda Blvd. in Tarzana. 
</P>
<P>
 The bagel brunch between 9:30 a.m. and 12:30 p.m. is sponsored by a young 
adult program of the Jewish Federation Council. Volunteers planning to 
participate are asked to call (213) 683-3433, day or night. 
</P>
<P>
 WATTS-AGOURA LINK: The Rev. John Coleman, pastor of Olivet Baptist Church in 
Watts, will preach on "last days" biblical interpretations at Agoura Bible 
Fellowship, 5564 Foothill Drive, during its 9:30 and 11 a.m. services Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Coleman has been heard for years on Christian radio -- on KKLA FM's "Night 
Light" program and on his own Sunday morning program on KGER AM. For 
information, call the Agoura church at (818) 889-7449. JOHN DART 
</P>
