<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 15 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Games lost: 14. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 195. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 474. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: 
</P>
<P>
 $66.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by owners: $127.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: None and no negotiating sessions are scheduled. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "The likelihood (on whether the rest of the season will be 
canceled) grows every day."  
</P>
<P>
 -- Donald Fehr, Union negotiator 
