<TEXT>
<P>
 Pats Lucky Charm, a winner of her last two starts for trainer H.J. Visscher, 
will go for a third consecutive victory in the $12,000 San Bernardino Overnight 
Handicap tonight at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 A 5-year-old First Down Dash mare, Pats Lucky Charm drew the outside post in 
the field of six older fillies and mares and will carry high weight of 123 
pounds.After beating $16,000 claimers by 1 1/4 lengths on July 7, Pats Lucky 
Charm returned to win an allowance race by three-quarters of a length on Aug. 
11. 
</P>
<P>
 The rest of the field, from the rail out, in the 400-yard race: High Class 
Gal, Awesome Blossom, Just A Wildone, The Pie Policy and No Policy Signed. 
</P>
<P>
