<TEXT>
<P>
 Ghost towns -- A story in Thursday's Times confused a drop in arrests with a 
drop in reports of major crimes at some San Fernando Valley "ghost towns" -- 
apartment buildings left vacant by quake damage. The story should have stated 
that homicides, rapes and other major crimes reported in the North Hills area 
east of the San Diego Freeway declined 30% during the first seven months of 
this year compared to the year before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
